---
const principles = [
  {
    title: "A personal front door",
    body: "The root of the domain is now free to become a proper personal site instead of pretending one app is the whole story.",
  },
  {
    title: "Apps with their own space",
    body: "Each product can either live under /apps/ on this domain or route outward if it deserves its own separate website.",
  },
  {
    title: "Motion that feels intentional",
    body: "Astro, CSS, and small progressive scripts are plenty for beautiful animation, layered visuals, and responsive effects without turning the site into a mess.",
  },
];
---

<section id="about" class="landing-section">
  <div class="landing-section__inner">
    <div class="section-heading" data-reveal>
      <p class="section-kicker">About</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The site can stay clean now and still grow into something richer later.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        This setup keeps the architecture simple without making the design feel flat. The root can
        become a proper personal site, while app pages keep a more product-shaped voice.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      {principles.map((principle, index) => (
        <article class="feature-card landing-surface" data-reveal style={`transition-delay:${index * 90}ms;`}>
          <p class="feature-card__count">0{index + 1}</p>
          <h3>{principle.title}</h3>
          <p>{principle.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
